<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7616471>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. – Sinningia ganevii Chautems & Mat. Perret. A. Habit, flowering stage; B. Longitudinal cut of corolla showing androecium and gynoecium; C. Ventral and dorsal view of coherent anthers; D. Ovary and nectary, corolla removed; E. Schematic arrangement of the nectary glands. [Chautems 550, G] [Drawing: G. Loza]" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7616471/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7616473>
    dc:description "Fig.2.– Distribution of Sinningia ganevii Chautems & Mat. Perret (black triangle) and S. sulphurea Chautems & D.B.O.S. Cardoso (black square), including their related species S. harleyi Wiehler & Chautems (white triangle) and S. barbata (Nees & Mart.) G. Nicholson (white square)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7616473/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7616475>
    dc:description "Fig. 3.– Image featuring the similar erect habit of Sinningia ganevii (left) and S. harleyi (right) and their distinct floral morphology corresponding to bee and hummingbird pollination syndrome, respectively. Cultivated in CJBG] [Photo: M. Perret]" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7616475/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

